新冠肺炎疫情不仅正在成为一场波及全球的健康危机，而且正在演变成一场经济危机并且对全球治理构成挑战新冠疫情考验全球治理本刊记者/安然发于2020.316总第939期《中国新闻周刊》布鲁斯·艾尔沃德是世卫组织总干事高级顾问，2月24日，他在考察中国采取的抗疫行动之后评价说，“面对一种未为人知的新型病毒，中国采取了恢弘、灵活和积极的防控措施。
The New Crown Pneumonia epidemic is not only becoming a global health crisis, but is also evolving into an economic crisis and challenging global governance.. Test of Global Governance Journalist / Enron Bruce Alvold, Senior Advisor to the Director-General of WHO, reviewed China's response to the epidemic on February 24 and said, "China has adopted a grand, flexible and proactive approach to control a new and unknown virus.
”如今，这样的措施已经显著地减缓了新冠病毒在中国国内的传播势头，但这种病毒传播到世界其他国家的形势，正在考验着不同公共卫生体系的应对能力。
Today, such measures have significantly slowed the spread of the virus in China, but its spread to other parts of the world is testing the ability of different public health systems to respond.
截至北京时间3月9日17时，中国以外新冠肺炎确诊病例数达到28673例，死亡686例。
By 1700 hours Beijing time on March 9, the number of confirmed cases of pneumonia outside China had reached 28,673, with 686 deaths.
其中，意大利确诊病例逼近1万；不仅如此，意大利新冠肺炎患者的死亡率突破5.04％，为全球最高，与之对应的死亡人数是463人。
Italy has nearly 10,000 confirmed cases, the highest death rate in the world at 5.04 percent, compared with 463 deaths.
在这些不断刷新的数字的带动下，疫情以意大利为中心正在向整个欧洲加速扩散。
Led by these constantly updated figures, the epidemic is spreading rapidly across Europe, with Italy at the center.
在美国，随着“至尊公主”号邮轮停靠在加州奥克兰港，全美已确诊至少687例新冠肺炎病例，其中包括死亡患者22例，疫情迅速蔓延至全美34个州和华盛顿特区。
In the United States, at least 687 cases of new crown pneumonia, including 22 deaths, have been confirmed across the United States as the USS Supreme Princess docked at Oakland Port, California, rapidly spreading to 34 states and Washington, D.C.
中东地区疫情也在持续蔓延。
Epidemics in the Middle East are also continuing.
3月9日，伊朗新增595例确诊病例，总数增至7161例，死亡病例增至237例。
On 9 March, there were 595 new confirmed cases in Iran, bringing the total to 7,161 and the number of deaths to 237.
受疫情影响，伊朗最高领袖哈梅内伊将取消新年致辞，以避免聚集增加病毒传播风险。
Affected by the outbreak, Iran's Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei will cancel his New Year's message to avoid gathering to increase the risk of spreading the virus.
为防范疫情，伊朗全国法院已批准释放大约7万名囚犯。
In an effort to prevent the outbreak, Iran's national courts have approved the release of some 70,000 prisoners.
与此同时，韩国每日新增确诊病例数在下降，在疫情严重的大邱和庆尚北道，病毒的蔓延出现了放缓势头，但仍在继续。
At the same time, the number of new confirmed cases per day is declining in South Korea, and the spread of the virus has slowed but continues in the severely affected Taegu and Gyeongshan provinces.
3月9日，世卫组织总干事谭德塞表示，新冠肺炎疫情已在许多国家出现，该疫情构成大流行的威胁“已经变得非常真实”。
The threat of a pandemic "has become very real" in many countries, WHO Director-General Theresa Tupper said March 9.
新冠肺炎疫情不仅正在成为一场波及全球的健康危机，而且正在演变成一场经济危机并且对全球治理构成挑战。
The New Crown Pneumonia epidemic is becoming not only a global health crisis, but also an economic crisis and a challenge to global governance.
起初对新型冠状病毒影响的预测总是令人想起2003年暴发的SARS，但如今越来越多的共识是，新冠疫情所带来的损害比SARS更大。
Early predictions of the impact of the new coronavirus were always reminiscent of the SARS outbreak in 2003, but there is now a growing consensus that the damage caused by the new outbreak is greater than that caused by SARS.
这不仅是因为这一新发传染病造成的死亡人数已经远超前者，而且其经济后果很可能与其他不利因素叠加在一起。
This is not only because the number of deaths caused by this new infectious disease has far exceeded that of the former, but its economic consequences are likely to be compounded by other adverse factors.
防御病毒扩散的应急措施导致了供应链中断和生产、服务的停顿。
Emergency measures to prevent the spread of the virus have led to supply chain disruption and disruption of production and services.
随着疫情的升级，它造成的全球冲击将比单纯的供应链中断更为严重。
As the epidemic escalates, the global impact will be more severe than a simple supply-chain disruption.
在美国，新冠疫情在全球蔓延的影响与油价暴跌形成叠加效应，引起美股暴跌，标普500指数在3月9日开盘下跌逾7％，触发熔断机制。
In the United States, the combined effect of the global spread of the new cap epidemic and the collapse in oil prices caused United States stocks to plummet, with the S & P 500 index falling by more than 7 per cent on March 9, triggering a meltdown.
目前来看，全球经济衰退的可能性急剧上升。
For now, the likelihood of a global recession is rising sharply.
各国政策制定者需要认识到，除了降息和财政刺激措施外，还要解决对全球供应链的巨大冲击，而这正是开展国际合作的好机会，而非自我封闭之时。
Policymakers need to recognize that, in addition to interest rate cuts and fiscal stimulus measures, there is a huge shock to global supply chains that is a good opportunity for international cooperation, not a time of self-imposed isolation.
新冠疫情引发的一个直接问题是，世界各国应如何组织起来应对传染病的威胁。
A direct question raised by the new Crown epidemic is how the world should organize itself to deal with the threat of infectious disease.
世界范围的疫情暴发进一步影响着人们如何看待全球化，以及对国际合作的思考。
Outbreaks worldwide have further influenced how globalization is perceived, as well as thinking about international cooperation.
与传染病作斗争的黄金法则是各国将信息及时公之于众。
The golden rule in the fight against infectious diseases is for States to make information publicly available in a timely manner.
例如，在疫情早期，中国科学家迅速鉴定出新冠病毒，并共享了该病毒的基因序列，从而促进了全球疫苗研发的合作。
For example, in the early days of the outbreak, Chinese scientists quickly identified the new crown virus and shared its genetic sequence, facilitating global cooperation in vaccine development.
随着新冠病毒在全球的继续传播，人类不得不依靠政府之间的合作来有效地抗击这种疾病。
As the new crown virus continues to spread around the world, humans have to rely on cooperation between governments to fight the disease effectively.
每隔几年，人类就会面对全球性的新发传染病。
Every few years, humanity is confronted with new and emerging infectious diseases on a global scale.
本世纪仅仅过了五分之一，就出现了SARS、H1N1流感、埃博拉、中东呼吸综合征（MERS）、寨卡病毒，以及眼前我们还有太多未知的新型冠状病毒。
Just over a fifth of this century has seen SARS, H1N1, Ebola, the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS), the Zika virus, and far too many new coronavirus unknown to us.
没人知道新冠疫情会持续多久，如果它没有随着北半球春季的到来而传染性下降，那么全世界的人们就必须等待疫苗开发和推广，才能让更多人进入“安全地带”。
No one knows how long the new crown will last, and if it does not decline with the onset of spring in the northern hemisphere, people around the world will have to wait for a vaccine to be developed and rolled out to bring more people into the "safe zone."
现代医药和健康水平已经大大降低了暴发传染病的频率，显著减缓了疾病的传播速度，同时降低了死亡率。
Modern medicine and health levels have significantly reduced the frequency of outbreaks of infectious diseases, slowed the spread of diseases significantly and reduced mortality.
目前，新冠病毒造成的总体死亡率约为3.4%左右，其中老年人和本来就有健康问题的人面临的死亡风险最高。
The overall mortality rate from the new crown virus is currently around 3.4 per cent, with older persons and those with pre-existing health problems at the highest risk of death.
而相比之下，早期现代意大利北部暴发的流行病，其死亡率高达30％~40％。
By contrast, the mortality rate from the early modern epidemics of northern Italy was as high as 30-40%.
传染病流行的预防和控制是一项全球公益事业，需要加强全球协作。
The prevention and control of infectious disease epidemics is a global public good that requires enhanced global collaboration.
传染病以不同的方式影响不同的国家，决策者必须相应地调整其应对方式。
Infectious diseases affect different countries in different ways, and policymakers must adapt their response accordingly.
与此同时，各国政府应当尽可能地采取旨在保护医疗工作者和弱势群体的措施。
At the same time, Governments should, to the extent possible, take measures aimed at protecting health workers and vulnerable groups.
纵观历史，危机与人类进步往往相伴而生。
Throughout history, crises have often accompanied human progress.
尽管日益猖獗的新冠病毒疫情可能会加深民族主义和孤立主义，并带来全球化的放缓，但另一方面，这次疫情暴发也可能刺激掀起新一轮的国际合作浪潮。
While a growing outbreak of the new crown virus could deepen nationalism and isolationism and slow globalization, it could also spur a new wave of international cooperation.
世界各国目前还在为减少新冠病毒带来的恐惧和损失而斗争，在此过程中，它将鼓励人们努力创造一个更好的全球化模式。
Countries around the world are still struggling to reduce the fear and loss of the new crown virus, and in doing so will encourage efforts to create a better model of globalization.
